    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-05-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1588.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch, No. 2901½, of the 2d ultimo, reporting that you have made a demand on
                    the Chinese Government that immediate action must be taken by it to carry out
                    the terms agreed upon by yourself and the Tsung-li Yamên for the settlement of
                    our claims growing out of the recent riot at Chiang Pei Ting.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your action in the matter and instructs you to follow up
                    the demand on the line of previous instructions in similar cases.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
